	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Nov 14th 4:27 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.20]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Actually it's fairly common knowledge now (unfortunately) that CHA is really, really overrated.&nbsp;&nbsp;All it effects is the chance of charm landing.  There's some speculation that it might effect the ability to land mez, but many high level enchanters have put this to the test with no real proof of it found.  CHA never effects the duration of a spell, and it doesn't effect Fear, Stun, or any other spell other than Charm (and in a much more limited way Mez).  It's unfortunate so many Chanters, going from a guide book, or just based on what's primary, buffed CHA up so high in lieu of other stats.  My chanter has a CHA of about 70.  Agi about 130, Intelligence around 180 now (level 36).  I never have any problem landing charms or mezzes (particularly if I first Tash).  I use a neg CHA weapon, a neg CHA secondary, hell, I never avoid neg CHA stuff if it boosts Intelligence or AC or Agi.  I see a lot of chanters get an item like the Tome of Dark Rituals (or whatever that Halloween book was called), and immediately shun it, sell it, bank it, whatever.  To me that's ridiculous.  CHA is overrated.  And this is becoming less and less of an opinion every day.<br>&nbsp;<br>Leafbringer, Pathfinder<br>Leafdefiler, Undead Enchanter<br>Leafcat, Once a pet.&nbsp;&nbsp;Once.</td></tr>
