	   <tr><td colspan=2>I don't pretend to be an expert on the subject, but I do see charisma playing a large role in charm duration. I play a 54 enchanter and I have several enchanter friends who have similar attitudes to yours towards charisma. I frequently solo in Skyfire by charming wurms and killing with them and my other chanter friends are amazed and say they would never do that because charm is so unstable for them and never lasts long enough to be worth it. My charms last pretty long as far as I can tell. Anywhere from 5 minutes up to 15 minutes, sometimes longer. When playing my alts and grouped with enchanters, they very very rarely charm and when they do, it doesn't last more than a couple minutes before it turns around and starts hitting them. I always ALWAYS have adorning grace on and I keep my int hovering around 210 and put up my charisma and mana instead of int whenever possible. But, to each his own I guess. 255 int is easy to get, even as a dark elf enchanter who put 20 points into charisma when she started. I don't regret it one bit.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Jun 18 22:59:28 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
